This directory is a single, self-contained browser visualizer: one HTML file with inline JS/CSS, no build step, no other source files or subdirectories. Its entire external contract is consuming `../out/viz-data.json` (produced by `target/debug/viz-data` elsewhere in the repo) and rendering it as a clickable stroke-tree explorer.

Since there is exactly one file, there is no cross-file coupling to describe within `viz/` — the coupling that matters is external, between `index.html`'s hardcoded JSON field assumptions (`categories`, `nodes[key].children/terminal/description/multiLine/oneLiner/oneLinerRoot/axis`) and whatever schema `viz-data` emits; that schema lives outside this directory, so a change on either side must be coordinated manually since there's no validation layer here to catch drift.

Any future addition to this directory (e.g. splitting the inline script into separate JS/CSS files, or adding a build step) should preserve the current state model described in `index.html.ctx` — `path`, `oneLinerActive`, `axisSelection`, singleton auto-chaining, and the self-healing truncation on invalid path entries — since that logic is the crux of correctness, not just presentation.

intent_divergence: no intent.md exists for this directory, so no divergence can be assessed.